OL,7,F"I had worked for the Public Burial
OL,8,FOffice in Damascus. My job was to
OL,9,Fissue receipts and coordinate
OL,10,Flogistics for families. I had never
OL,11,Fdealt with corpses.
OL,13,F"Then one day, my manager called me
OL,14,Finto his office. Two men were waiting.
OL,15,FThey told me to go with them."
OL,17,FMohammad was taken to the Najha
OL,18,Fcemetery, just south of the capital.
OL,20,F"I couldn't say no."
